[{"id":"VR724605","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"Two figures are labeled Figure 1 and Figure 2. Each figure shows the same two blocks labeled A and B on a horizontal surface with a spring attached to block B. Figure 1 shows the spring compressed between the two blocks as they are held close together. Figure 2 shows the blocks released and moving away from each other.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR724605.g01.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two blocks, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>B</mtext></math></span></span>, are at rest on a horizontal surface. A spring is attached to Block <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>B</mtext></math></span></span> and is compressed when the blocks are held together, as shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>. The blocks are then simultaneously released and move in opposite directions along the surface with negligible friction as shown in Figure <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>. Which of the following correctly indicates how the total kinetic energy and total momentum of the spring-two-cart system change as the blocks move away from each other just after they are released compared to these quantities before they are released?</p><div class=\"table_wrapper\"><table class=\"tgroup cols:3 colsep:0 frame:none rowsep:0\"><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col1 colnum:1 colsep:1 colwidth:45\"/><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col2 colnum:2 colwidth:160\"/><col class=\"colspec align:center colname:col3 colnum:3 colwidth:150\"/><thead class=\"thead\"><tr class=\"row rowsep:1\"><th class=\"entry colname:col1\"></th><th class=\"entry colname:col2\">Total Kinetic Energy</th><th class=\"entry colname:col3\">Total Momentum</th></tr></thead><tbody class=\"tbody\"><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">A</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Increases</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Stays the same</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">B</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Increases</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Increases</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">C</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Stays the same</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Stays the same</td></tr><tr class=\"row\"><td class=\"entry colname:col1\">D</td><td class=\"entry colname:col2\">Stays the same</td><td class=\"entry colname:col3\">Increases</td></tr></tbody></table></div>\n","rubricRef":"VR724605_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">B</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">C</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">D</p>"],"answer":0}]